					Biographies





Name
Description




							Mahmoud Mahmoud


					
							Dr. Mahmoud Ahmad Abdul Rahman Mahmoud serves as Non-Executive Chairman of the Board at Kuwait Telecommunications Company K.S.C.P, representing Kuwait Investment Authority since 2016. He was Chairman of the Board at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC, representing Kuwait Investment Authority since March 31, 2015. He has experience in higher education sector and legal work serving many governmental and public entities. After graduation, he joined as teaching staff in College of Law. He was appointed as Legal Affairs Director in Kuwait University for one year. From 1997 till 2005 he served as Head of Legal Office at Kuwait Civil Aviation Directorate, from 2002 till 2004, served as Assistant Dean of College of Law at Kuwait University. Since 2005 till date, Dr. Mahmoud serves as Legal Department Director at Kuwait Investment Authority, Member of the Board at Warba Bank and Health Insurance Hospitals Company. Moreover, he has published several legal theses in Law magazine and other scientific magazines as well as implemented two projects in respect of consumer protection and monopoly and merger Law. He holds a Ph D in Commercial Law from University of Exeter, UK in 1994 and Bachelor degree from Kuwait University in 1998.




							Salman Al Badran


					
							Eng. Salman Abdul Aziz Al Badran serves as Chief Executive Officer at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC since January 2011. He has more than fifteen years of experience in Telecommunications and GSM cellular networks, and expertise in infrastructure implementation and operations management. He also worked as Chief Technical Officer at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC. Prior to joining the Company, Eng. Al Badran acted as the General Manager of Al Jawal Network at Saudi Telecom Company. He holds a Bachelor's degree in Applied Electrical Engineering from King Fahd University of Petroleum & Minerals, with a specialization in the field of Communication and Power.




							Khalid Bayari


					
							Dr. Khalid Bin Hussein Bayari serves as Non-Executive Vice Chairman of the Board at Kuwait Telecommunications Company K.S.C.P, representing Saudi Telecom Co since 2016. He was Vice Chairman of the Board at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC, representing Saudi Telecom Co. He started his career in Academia as associate professor at King Fahd University of Petroleum and Minerals between 1990 - 1995 where he acted as supervisor of many thesis and dissertations and engaged in research and teaching assignments and projects. He also published during this period, scores of research papers in International journals and periodicals. Dr. Bayari began working in private sector as Senior Vice President at Advanced Electronics Company Limited in 1995. Since May, 20013, he serves as Senior Vice President of Technology and Operation at Saudi Telecom Group. He serves as Member of the board at many companies like Oger Telecom, Türk Telekom, AveA Co and Electricity and Cogeneration Regulatory Authority (ECRA) Saudi Arabia and Chairman of Awl Company. He is currently a Member of International Committee, which supervises Center of Excellency in Nanotechnology affiliated with King Fahd University of Petroleum, Saudi Arabia. He worked as branch President of IEEE in Saudi Arabia. He holds PhD in Electrical Engineering from University of Southern California in 1990, Bachelors, and Masters in Electrical Engineering from King Fahd University of Petroleum and Minerals.




							Abdulaziz Al Qatie


					
							Mr. Abdulaziz Abdullah Al Qatie serves as Chief Financial Officer at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC since August 2008. Before joining the Company, he was Vice President of Finance for Arabian Internet & Communications Services Co. - Awalnet in Saudi Arabia from 2006 until 2008. Previously, he held various roles at Al-Faisaliah Group Holding Company Ltd. He has a BA in Accounting from King Saud University and holds various professional certificates including Certified Financial Consultant (CFC) from Institute of Financial Consultants in 2008, Certified Accounting Technician (CAT) from Institute of Accounting Technicians in 2008 and Certified Cost Controller (CCC) from American Academy of Financial Management in 2005.




							Zarar Khan


					
							Mr. Zarar Khan serves as Chief Technology Officer at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC since January 2011. He joined the company in 2008 as Network Director and continued in this position till 2011. He has over 15 years of experience in telecommunications and technology sector. Prior to coming to the company, Mr. Khan worked at Orascom Telecom in various roles with the last one being the Director for Network Performance. He holds a Bachelors of Engineering Degree in Electrical Engineering from The Ghulam Ishaq Khan (GIK) Institute of Engineering Sciences and Technology.




							Ramez Sabawi







							Wassim El Hayek







							Issam Al Asousi


					
							Mr. Issam Essa Al Asousi serves as Chief Corporate Affairs Officer at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC since October 2011. He started his career in the banking sector 22 years ago. He took up his first post in 1980 with the Bank of Kuwait and Middle East (later renamed as Al Ahli United Bank) where he was in charge of the Consumer Sector. Later, he joined Al Dar Investment Company in 2003 where he was instrumental in driving the organization's investment strategies, including the establishment of a Consumer Finance Company called WARAD. In 2008, Mr. Al Asousi moved on to Al Dowalliah Investment Group where he was appointed as Deputy Managing Director. He has graduated from Kuwait University in 1975 with a degree in Commerce. In 1981, he completed 1-year training program at Chase Manhattan Bank in Washington. He has also completed a Diploma in Banking from Kuwait Institute of Banking Studies in 1982.




							Anas Al Ateeqi


					
							Mr. Anas Yousef Hamad Al Ateeqi serves as Chief Human Resource Officer at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC since December 2013. He has an experience in Human Resources for more than 16 years. Prior to joining the company, he was Chief Human Resources Officer and Group Head of Human Capital, Support Services & Administration at Warba Bank. Mr. Al Ateeqi has a BA in Economics & Business Administration from the Kuwait University and MBA in Enterprise Management from American University of Middle East.




							Sattam Al Douiakh







							Abdulrazzaq Al Essa







							Meshaal Al-Munaikh







							Monzer Al-Saleh







							Andrew Hanna


					
							Mr. Andrew Hanna is Chief Commercial Officer at Kuwait Telecommunications Company K.S.C.P since May 2016. Prior to joining the Company, he was Chief Commercial Officer at Kuwait Telecommunications Company, Bahrain since 2010 and before that, he was General Manager for Batelco Group, Bahrain and prior to this, he was General Manager for Enterprise and Government. He held other roles in technology sector including Chief Commercial and Operations Officer at Kalam Telecom Holding, Bahrain, Regional Manager at Microsoft MENA, General Manager for Alliances and Channels with Telecom New Zealand and National Manager of Strategy, Marketing for Ericsson Australia in addition to various senior product management, marketing, sales and strategy roles with Telstra Australia. Mr. Hanna is Chairman of the Chief Marketing Officers Committee of the SAMENA Telecom Council. He holds Bachelors degree in Economics and Commerce from Victoria University, MBA in Marketing and Postgraduate Diploma in International Business from Monash University, Australia. He is alumni of Stanford Graduate School of Business and London Business School.




							Ziyad Al Khwaiter


					
							Eng. Ziyad Al Khwaiter serves as Non-Executive Member of the Board at Kuwait Telecommunications Company K.S.C.P, representing Gulf STC Holding 3 since 2016. He was Member of the Board at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC, representing Gulf STC Holding 3 until 2016. He started his work in the field of Software Engineering and Application Development and Systems Analysis, where he worked at the Arab Center for Security Studies and Training, then at SABIC until 1993. After that, he worked as director of the Center for Computer and Information Systems Technology of National Central Library in Saudi Arabia. In 2000, he joined Saudi Telecom Co as Projects Manager and then in 2008, he joined Communications and Information Technology Commission as Senior Consultant for organizations Communications and Information Technology. In the end of 2009, he joined Integrated Telecom Co and served as President of Regulatory sector and then Vice President of Regulatory Affairs sector and Business Continuity sector . In October 2013, he was appointed as General Manager of Regulatory Affairs at Saudi Telecom Co, a position he holds currently. Eng. Al Khwaiter holds a Bachelor of Science in Computer Science from King Saud University.




							Moaeed Al Saloom


					
							Mr. Moaeed Ben Huwaij Al Saloom serves as Non-Executive Member of the Board at Kuwait Telecommunications Company K.S.C.P, representing Gulf STC Holding 1 since 2016. He was Member of the Board at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC, representing Gulf STC Holding 1 till 2016. He is Vice President of Investment Operations at Saudi Telecom Group. He started his career as Manager of the Networks design Unit at Saudi Telecom Co and held various positions like Customer Service Manager, Field Operations Manager and Public Sector Sales Manager until 2010 when he was appointed as General Manager for Operations in Investment Division. In 2008, he also worked as Chief Commercial Officer at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC. Mr. Al Saloom serves as Member of the Board at VIVA, Bahrain. He holds Bachelor’s in Electrical Engineering from King Fahd University of Petroleum and Minerals in 1992 and a Masters degree in Business Administration from Prince Sultan University in 2013.




							Ameen Al Shiddi


					
							Mr. Ameen Bin Fahad bin Abdul Aziz Al Shiddi serves as Non-Executive Member of the Board at Kuwait Telecommunications Company K.S.C.P, representing Gulf STC Holding since 2016. He was Member of the Board at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC, representing Gulf STC Holding till 2016. He joined the Saudi Telecom in 2001 and held various positions until he promoted as Senior President of Finance, a position he holds currently. He holds Bachelors in Management from King Saud University and Masters in Accounting from Southwest Missouri State, USA. He is Certified Public Accountant from Saudi Organization for Certified Public Accountants and Certified Management Accountant.




							Ahmad Al Turki


					
							Mr. Ahmad Abdullah Ali Al Turki serves as Non-Executive Member of the Board at Kuwait Telecommunications Company K.S.C.P, representing Public Institution for Social Security since 2016. He was Member of the Board at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC, representing Public Institution for Social Security till 2016. He started his career as Engineer of trainee systems and sequence at Public Institution for Social Security in 1985 and subsequently became Vice Director General of automated Processing and Information, a post he holds currently. He holds a Bachelors degree in Business Administration and Computer Science sub-specialty in 1985. He also attended many training courses in technical, financial and commercial fields, which were held at international levels.




							Salah Al-Fouzan


					
							Mr. Salah Ahmad Meshari Al-Fouzan is Independent Member of the Board at Kuwait Telecommunications Company K.S.C.P since May 2016. He began his career at Mobile Telecommunications Co in 1997, initially holding positions in the Telecommunications/Network Engineering Division in Group's subsidiary in Kuwait, and subsequently transitioning to Business Planning and Strategy Development at Group level in 2002. In 2008, he became Chief Business Development Officer and oversaw mergers and acquisitions, geographical expansion and adjacent business development activities for the group, including wireless broadband initiatives. Mr. Al Fouzan served on the Boards of Kuwait Airways, Celtel Nigeria Limited, Celtel Kenya and Zain in Ghana. Currently he is Member of the Board at Equity Investment Holding in Egypt. He holds a Bachelor of Science degree in Electrical Engineering from Gannon University in Pennsylvania in 1997 and Diploma in Business Administration from Bradford University, United Kingdom.




							Abdul Aziz Al Qassar


					
							Dr. Abdul Aziz Khalifa Al Qassar serves as Chairman of the Shariah Supervisory Board of at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC. He is a professor at the College of Fiqh and Department of Sharia and Islamic Studies, University of Kuwait, where he has been Deputy Dean for Academic Affairs, since 2002. He was involved in transforming Kuwait Real Estate Bank (conventional Bank) into a full Islamic Bank. Dr. Al Qassar is a member of Sharia supervisory boards of many banks and financial institutions and published more than a dozen of scientific researches. He holds doctorate degree in Fiqh and Islamic Jurisprudence, Master's degree in Islamic Studies from Al-Azhar University and Bachelor's degree in Shariah from Kuwait University.




							Ali Al-Rashed







							Issa Issa


					
							Dr. Issa Zaki Issa is Member of the Shariah Supervisory Board at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCC. He is an Assistant Professor at the College of Basic Education, Public Authority for Applied Education and Training, Kuwait. He chairs and is a member of several Shariah supervisory boards including the Ministry of Awqaf and Islamic Affairs Kuwait, Zakat House, and the Kuwait Awqaf Public Foundation. He is also a specialized trainer in Shariah courses and a regular speaker at Islamic conferences and forums. Dr. Issa has authored many books and publications on matters relating to Islamic Jurisprudence. He holds a PhD, Masters and Bachelor's degree from Islamic University in Madinah.











