                                                Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCP
                                             Company Snapshot
                                            









                                            
	Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCP operates in the Radiotelephone communications sector.
	
	In addition to historical fundamental analyses, the complete report available to purchase compares Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCP with three other
	telecommunications providers in Middle East:
		
	Bahrain Telecommunications Company BSC
	
		of Bahrain
		(2016
	sales of 367.13 million Bahranine Dinars [US$973.82  million]
		),
	
	Partner Communications Company  Limited
	
		of Israel
		(3.54 billion Israel Shekels [US$995.23  million]
		of which 80%
		was Cellular Segment), and
	
	Cellcom Israel Ltd.
	
		which is
		
			also
		
		based in Israel
		(4.03 billion Israel Shekels [US$1.13  billion]
		of which 74%
		was Cellcom).
	
	Sales Analysis. 
	Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCP reported sales of 279.06 million Kuwaiti Dinars  (US$924.04 million)
		for the
		
		year ending
		December of 2016.
	
		This
		
			represents
		
				a very small
			
			increase of 0.8%
		
		 versus 2015, when the company's sales were 276.89 million Kuwaiti Dinars .
	
			Sales at Kuwait Telecommunications Company KSCP have increased during each of the previous five years
		
		(and since 2011, sales have increased a total of 198%).
	

	




 


 
 


 
 


 
 











 



 













 










